    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - ELECTRONIC ENGINES, CATERPILLAR C-10 AND C-12
        ENGINES - OPERATION - Vehicle Speed Sensor
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Vehicle Speed Sensor</title>
        <para>The ECM receives the AC signal from the vehicle speed sensor (531) on circuits 97AJ and 97AK, through
            connector (1014), and sends a signal to the vehicle speedometer. The ECM also sends the signal to drive the
            vehicle tachometer.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
